S. Korean Military Authorities Denounced 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- Yun Kwang Ung, minister of National Defence of south Korea, at a symposium held at the "National Assembly" on Sept. 15 said that he would keep Jaitun unit stationed in Arbil, Iraq, next year, too, according to south Korean MBC.
 All the fellow countrymen are now strongly demanding the immediate withdrawal of the south Korean troops from Iraq, bitterly denouncing the south Korean military authorities for their criminal acts of serving as a shock brigade of the U.S. imperialists' war of aggression. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 However, the south Korean military authorities' balderdash is not only an open challenge to the public demand at home and abroad but also a reckless act betraying their bellicose character again. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Openly asserting that experience of actual war in Iraq will become hard core in pressurizing the north, the bellicose elements of south Korea have conducted all military operations there under the simulated conditions of "emergency" in the Korean Peninsula. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean military authorities' assertion is no more than an open revelation of their ulterior intention to accumulate more combat experience in Iraq to provide for a war of aggression against the north. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The south Korean military authorities should stop their provocative preparations for a war of aggression against the north and immediately withdraw their troops from Iraq.

U.S. New Doctrine for Use of Nukes under Fire 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- The DPRK can not but take a serious view of the U.S. new doctrine for the use of nuclear weapons as it makes it possible to mount a preemptive nuclear attack on any target in any region any moment according to decision of a commander of the U.S. forces
 Commenting on this, Minju Joson Thursday says that the DPRK can not but take issue with the U.S. double-dealing approach towards the international nuclear non-proliferation regime. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The news analyst goes on: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. has posed a constant threat of a preemptive nuclear attack to the DPRK and other anti-imperialist independent countries while pursuing the vertical proliferation of nuclear weapons including the research and development of smaller nukes in a bid to carry out with ease its strategy of world domination based on unchallenged edge in the field of strategic and tactical nuclear weapons. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is, therefore, quite natural for a number of countries to take countermeasures for self-defense as their existence is exposed to the threat of the U.S. constant nuclear blackmailing. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. needs and values the nuclear non-proliferation regime so much it would be proper for it to make a bold switchover in its criminal nuclear policy.
 The U.S. pressurizes other countries to return to the NPT, while posing a grave nuclear threat to them behind the scene. This contradictory arrogant attitude is a typical example of double-dealing tactics. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Washington might know well what sort of fate the NPT would face and what serious situation could be created in the world should it pursue its ambition to launch a nuclear war and its policy of threatening other countries with nukes. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 If the U.S. truly opts for this, it may go its own way while allowing others to go their own ways. But there is one thing the U.S. should bear in mind. In that case the U.S. will be entirely accountable for the breach of the world non-proliferation regime.

Anniversary of Union of Korean Students in Japan Marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Tokyo, September 20 (KNS-KCNA) -- A meeting took place in Tokyo on Sept. 17 to mark the 60th anniversary of the formation of the Union of Korean Students in Japan.
 Read out at the meeting was a message of greetings sent by the Korean Student Committee. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Ho Jong Man, chief vice-chairman of the Central Standing Committee of the General Association of Korean Residents in Japan, in his congratulatory speech referred to the fact that President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il showed deep care for the work of the union, adding that it has performed shining feats for the country and the nation and the compatriots. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Jo Tu Song, chairman of the union, in a report expressed the union's will to train competent patriotic intellectuals contributing to the building of a great prosperous powerful reunified nation and a harmonious and united community of Koreans and thus advance the movement of the Korean students studying in Japanese universities on a fresh basis. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Introduced at the meeting were congratulatory letters sent by several universities of the DPRK and the Joson University Committee of the Korean Youth League in Japan and others. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A video tape on the 60 year-long history of the union was shown at the meeting before a performance was given on the occasion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Prior to the meeting, a photo exhibition took place.

Anniversary of General Bureau of Civil Aviation Marked 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- The Korean General Bureau of Civil Aviation marked its golden jubilee.
 With a deep insight into the importance of the air transport in building a rich and prosperous country, President Kim Il Sung founded the Korean General Bureau of Civil Aviation (then the Korean Civil Aviation Administration) on September 21, Juche 44 (1955) and made great efforts to build up it as the nation's reliable air transport base.
 Supreme Commander Kim Jong Il, always paying deep attention to the work of the general bureau, has given on-the-spot guidance to it on hundreds of occasions to clearly indicate the orientation and ways of building the Juche-based civil aviation and develop it into modern civil aviation with various types of airliners and equipment.
 A meeting marking the anniversary of the general bureau was held on the spot Wednesday. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A congratulatory message of the Central Military Commission of the Workers' Party of Korea was conveyed to the whole staff of the general bureau at the meeting.
 The staff of the civil aviation have ensured the external activities of Kim Il Sung and Kim Jong Il to the last detail in a responsible manner in the spirit of devotedly defending the leader and provided a sure guarantee for the security of foreign airliners flying in the sky above the DPRK, thus contributing to enhancing the international authority of the Party and the leader and glorifying the dignity and honor of Juche Korea, the congratulatory message said. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It highly praised the staff of the general bureau for their great achievements made in the course of carrying out their revolutionary tasks by displaying intense loyalty to the Party and the leader and patriotic devotion. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A report was made by Kang Ki Sop, director of the general bureau. Then followed speeches. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A message of pledge to Kim Jong Il was adopted at the meeting.

More Live-Stock Breeding Centers Built
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, September 22 (KCNA) -- A lot of modern live-stock breeding centers have been built in different parts of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea.
 Many efforts have been channeled into industrialization and intensification of stockbreeding to put it on a scientific and modern basis despite economic difficulties. As a result, many stockbreeding and poultry farms have been built to increase the meat, egg and milk production. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 In hearty response to the intention of the Workers' Party of Korea to further improve the people's dietary life, servicepersons have constructed the cattle Farm in Songam, Chicken Farm No.112, Hwangju, September 27 and Anju Chicken Farms and so on. And the construction of several pig farms has been completed in Taehongdan and Samjiyon Counties for the purpose of solving the issues of meat and manure.
  Following the patriotic devotion of servicepersons, working people in Jagang and North Phyongan Provinces built modern chicken farms as models of the new century and those in Pyongyang also reconstructed the Mangyongdae, Sopho and other chicken farms along a modern line. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Meanwhile, people in Pyongyang, South Hamgyong, South and North Hwanghae and other provinces have dynamically pushed ahead with the construction of goat farms with a goal of raising herbivorous domestic animals in an extensive way.
 A number of large goat-breeding centers have made their appearance. Among them are the Kyenam Stockbreeding Farm, Goat Branch Farm attached to the Unjong Stockbreeding Co-op Farm under the Rural Economy Committee of North Hwanghae Province and General Stockbreeding Branch Farm of the Namsan Co-op Farm in Kusong City. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
  Duck and ostrich farms have been set up in different places of the country.
